{
  "text": "We test 21 traces from 3 random users with various velocities and directions to analyze the meta trajectory accuracy. We can get a mean velocity error of 1.7m/s, and a turning angle error of 5 \u2022 , which are competitive in inertial-based localization methods. Then we turn to the localization accuracy of the coordinate transformation algorithm in Groupon. Groupon can achieve a sub-meter accuracy with smartphones. The mean velocity error and locating error are depicted in Figure 4 . Since this part of experiment is detailed in Trail [CITATION_1] , the repetitious details need not be given here.",
  "correct_citation": {
